Guinness Peat Group Plc &lt;GNSP.L> hasarranged to receive a 125 mln dlr five year cash advancefacility, said Barclays de Zoete Wedd Ltd and Guinness Mahonand Co Ltd as joint arrangers.    The two firms said the terms of the facility will bereviewed after the third year with a view to consideringextension by a further two years.    The facility will include a tender panel to bid formulti-currency cash advances at a maximum rate of 0.1875 pctover the London Interbank Offered Rate.    The facility will incorporate an underwriting fee of 0.10pct in addition to a fee of 0.05 to 0.10 pct depending on theparticipation amount. In addition, Barclays and Guinness Mahonhave been named joint dealers for a complementary 100 mln dlreuro-commercial paper program.    Funds will be used to refinance the cost of the recentForstmann-Leff Associates acquisition as well as for generalcorporate purposes. REUTER&#3;